# CLAUDE.md — {{ project_name }}

Always use Spec-Driven Development in this repository.

Before making any changes, identify the active spec and read in this order:

1. `.specify/memory/constitution.md`
2. `.specify/specs/<active-spec>/spec.md`
3. `.specify/specs/<active-spec>/plan.md`
4. `.specify/specs/<active-spec>/tasks.md`

## Rules

- Treat `.specify/` as the source of truth.
- Do not implement features not described in `spec.md`.
- Follow `plan.md` for architecture and sequencing.
- Work task by task based on `tasks.md`.
- Only work on pending checks (`- [ ]`) and mark them when truly complete.
- If no tasks are pending, do not re-implement: validate consistency between constitution, spec, plan, tasks, and existing code.
- After each change, explain what task was completed and which files were modified.

## Prompts

Reusable prompts are in `.specify/prompts/`.
Custom prompts are in `.specify/prompts/custom/`.

Use `sdd prompt list` to see all available prompts.
Use `sdd prompt run <name> --var KEY=VALUE` to render and run a prompt.

